INSERT INTO `xdkstf_posts` VALUES (2,1,'2014-12-02 20:16:03','2014-12-02 20:16:03','','Holly Hill-1','','inherit','open','open','','holly-hill-1','','','2014-12-02 20:16:03','2014-12-02 20:16:03','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Holly-Hill-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3,1,'2014-12-02 20:16:08','2014-12-02 20:16:08','','Holly Hill-4','','inherit','open','open','','holly-hill-4','','','2014-12-02 20:16:08','2014-12-02 20:16:08','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Holly-Hill-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4,1,'2014-12-02 20:43:18','2014-12-02 20:43:18','','Children’s Campus Now Open','','publish','closed','closed','','slide-1','','','2014-12-21 23:14:19','2014-12-22 04:14:19','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?post_type=hh_homepage_slider&#038;p=4',3,'hh_homepage_slider','',0),(5,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p>Life can be very difficult to navigate. For many reasons, we sometimes choose a path that leads us away from our happiness. This path may have many obstacles that keep us from getting back on track. But at Holly Hill Hospital we know that there is a path to wellness and happiness inside each and every one of us, and that it cannot be taken way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Holly Hill, we are here to help you or your loved one get back on the best path to wellness. With a staff of clinicians experienced in the fields of mental health and addiction, Holly Hill is a source of support for our patients, their families and the communities we serve.</p>\r\n\r\nLocated in Raleigh, North Carolina, Holly Hill has equipped patients with the skills needed to return to their communities healthier and happier for more than 35 years. At our Adult Campus we treat only patients are ages 18 and older and our facility boasts features such as a gymnasium and outdoor green spaces. Patients under the age of 18 will be seen at our <a title=\"Child &amp; Adolescent Campus\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/\">children’s campus</a>.\r\n\r\nFor more information about our mental health or substance abuse treatment programs please call us now at 800-447-1800.','About Our Adult Campus','','publish','open','open','','about-our-adult-campus','','','2014-12-10 23:25:39','2014-12-10 23:25:39','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/',0,'page','',0),(6,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<a href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mm-head-shot.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-354 alignright\" src=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mm-head-shot-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"mm-head-shot\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Welcome to Holly Hill Hospital. For over 35 years, the Holly Hill name has been one of comfort and quality and I’m proud to say that we are constantly evolving, growing and enriching our programs to continue in this tradition of providing excellence in clinical behavioral health care.\r\n\r\nIt is our priority at Holly Hill to provide our patients with the treatment and resources needed to return to their communities as healthier individuals. To accomplish this goal I am joined by a team of clinical leaders who are experts in their field and share the vision and passion necessary to provide the best possible programming for the patients in our care. As a community resource, we also provide around the clock, no cost assessments to ensure that those who need services can find the appropriate placement and level of care.\r\n\r\nWe hope that our site provides you with the information you need as you search for help for yourself or loved one. I invite you to contact us today with questions or to receive more information on our programs and treatment team.\r\n\r\n<em>Sincerely,</em>\r\n\r\nMichael S. McDonald, Jr.\r\nChief Executive Officer – Managing Director','​CEO Welcome','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8bceo-welcome','','','2014-12-22 16:45:43','2014-12-22 21:45:43','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/%e2%80%8bceo-welcome/',1,'page','',0),(7,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','','Programs','','trash','open','open','','programs','','','2014-12-08 19:00:12','2014-12-08 19:00:12','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/programs/',2,'page','',0),(8,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">At Holly Hill Hospital, we encourage families to be an active part of their loved one’s treatment and recovery. Visiting hours and group family sessions are two of the ways you can support a loved one in treatment at our facility.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>General Visitation &amp; Phone Rules</b></span></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A confidential ID number is issued to each patient at the time of admission. Due to patient confidentiality, only the adult patient or legal guardian of a minor patient may give out this number.  Any visitor calling or coming in must have the ID number.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">All visitors will be required to present valid identification prior to visiting. </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No more than 2 visitors are allowed at one time.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Children under the age of 13 may not visit.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Phone call duration may be limited based on the therapy schedule. Patients may not make or receive phone calls during group times.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Day of Discharge: The therapist will coordinate a discharge date based on the individualized treatment plan. Please note that all discharges occur before 11:00am and transportation needs must be arranged prior to that time.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>1 South Visiting Hours:</b></span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tuesday Family Group, 9:30 – 11:30 a.m., *Family group is from 10:00 – 11:00 a.m. You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Thursday, 9:30 – 11:30 a.m., *Family group is from 10:00 – 11:00 a.m. You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, 9:30 – 11:30 a.m. and 6:00 – 8:00 p.m.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 9:30 – 11:30 a.m</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>1 East Visiting Hours:</b></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday, 6:30 – 8:00 p.m.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday Family Group, 1:30 – 4:00 p.m. *Family group is from 1:30 – 2:30 p.m.  You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 9:00 a.m – 11:00 a.m.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>1 West Visiting Hours:</b></span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Monday, 6:30 – 8:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Wednesday, 1:30 – 3:00 p.m. *Family group is from 1:30 – 2:30 p.m.  You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Friday, 6:30 – 8:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, 9:00 a.m. – 11:00 a.m.\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 1:30 – 4:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>1 North A&amp;B Visiting Hours:</b></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Wednesday, 7:00 – 8:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li>Thursday Family Group, 1:30 – 3:00 p.m. *Family group is from 1:30 – 2:30 p.m.  You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Friday, 7:00 – 8:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, 2:00 – 3:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 9:30 – 10:30 a.m.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>2 West Visiting Hours:</b></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tuesday, 1:30 – 3:00 p.m. *Family Group is from 1:30-2:30p.m. You must attend family group to be eligible for this visitation</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Thursday, 7:00 – 8:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, 1:30 – 3:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 1:30 – 3:00 p.m.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>2 East Visiting Hours:</b></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, 1:30 – 3:30 p.m.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Sunday, 1:30 – 3:30 p.m.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','Visiting Hours & Phone Times','','publish','open','open','','visiting-hours-phone-times','','','2014-12-21 22:46:09','2014-12-22 03:46:09','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/visiting-hours-phone-times/',3,'page','',0),(9,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','At Holly Hill Hospital, we know that it is our people who make the difference in the lives of our patients. Each of our employees, from mental health technicians and nurses to doctors and therapists, have the heart and training to provide consistently excellent care.\r\n\r\nLeading our team of talented individuals is a medical staff of impressive acclaim.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Collectively, our medical staff has over 100 years of psychiatric, inpatient hospital experience.</li>\r\n	<li>All of our psychiatrists have held appointments at University Medical Centers as teachers in psychiatry.</li>\r\n	<li>Our medical staff has published over 40 articles in medical journals.</li>\r\n	<li>In addition to psychiatry, more than half of our medical staff has significant medical care experience including work as emergency care physicians.</li>\r\n	<li>Our medical staff is experienced with treatment in a VA Hospital setting as well as enlisted military treatment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n<h2>Medical Staff:</h2>\r\n<div>[simple-staff-list group=\"Medical Staff\"]</div>\r\n</div>','Our Medical Team','','publish','open','open','','our-medical-team','','','2014-12-21 22:45:13','2014-12-22 03:45:13','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/our-medical-team/',4,'page','',0),(10,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','','Admissions & Assessments','','trash','open','open','','admissions-assessments','','','2014-12-08 19:00:50','2014-12-08 19:00:50','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/admissions-assessments/',5,'page','',0),(11,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p class=\"western\"><a href=\"http://www.jointcommission.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-260 size-full\" src=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/joint-commission-logo.jpg\" alt=\"Joint Commission Gold Logo\" width=\"100\" height=\"101\" /></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Holly Hill Hospital is fully licensed by the state of North Carolina and is accredited by the <a href=\"http://www.jointcommission.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Joint Commission</a>.</span></span></span></p>','​Licensing & Accreditation','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8blicensing-accreditation','','','2014-12-11 11:31:36','2014-12-11 16:31:36','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/%e2%80%8blicensing-accreditation/',6,'page','',0),(12,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Please fill out the form below to make a secure payment to Holly Hill Hospital. Note the First Name and Last Name should be the payer responsible for paying your invoice. If there are any questions or concerns please call us at 800.447.1800.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\nvar l2pButtonText = \'Pay Now\';\r\nvar l2pCustomWrapperStyles = {\r\n  \"background\": \"#ffffff\",\r\n  \"border-color\": \"#ffffff\",\r\n  \"border-style\": \"solid\",\r\n  \"border-width\": \"2px\",\r\n  \"width\": \"400px\"\r\n};\r\nvar l2pCustomLabelStyles = {\r\n  \"color\" : \"#222222\"\r\n};\r\nvar l2pWidgetCustomFields = {\'fields\':[{\'label\':\'Address\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'City\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'State\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Zip\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Phone\',\'type\':7,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Relationship\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient First Name\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient Last Name\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient Account No\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true}]};\r\n// do not modify these values!\r\nvar l2pClientId = \'2f2b265625d76a6704b08093c652fd79\';\r\nvar l2pWidgetId = \'1568\';\r\n</script>\r\n<script id=\"l2p-widget-script\" type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://www.linked2pay.com/l2p/widgets/paymentForm/js/load.js\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"l2p-widget-wrapper\"></div>\r\n','Pay Your Bill','','publish','open','open','','pay-your-bill','','','2014-12-08 16:11:11','2014-12-08 16:11:11','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/pay-your-bill/',7,'page','',0),(13,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<h2 class=\"western\">Adult Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 18 and over should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">3019 Falstaff Road</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7000</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax:919.231.5302</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/directions/\">Directions</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"western\">Children’s Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 17 and younger should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">201 Michael J Smith Lane</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7600</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax: 919.250.6724</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/directions/\"><i>Directions</i></a></p>','Contact Us','','trash','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-08 19:02:06','2014-12-08 19:02:06','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/contact-us/',8,'page','',0),(14,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','','Careers','','trash','open','open','','careers','','','2014-12-08 19:00:58','2014-12-08 19:00:58','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/about-our-adult-campus/careers/',9,'page','',0),(15,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">As a leader in behavioral healthcare, Holly Hill Hospital is committed to providing our patients with treatment programs that can help put them on a more solid path to recovery. Regardless of the program in which they are enrolled, our patients can expect quality treatment provided by a thoughtful and compassionate staff.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">To learn more about how Holly Hill can help you or your loved one, please choose a link below.</span></p>\r\n<a title=\"Mental Health\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/mental-health/\">Adults</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Geriatrics\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/geriatrics/\">Geriatrics</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Substance Abuse\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/substance-abuse/\">Substance Abuse</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Adult Outpatient (PHP)\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/adult-outpatient-php/\">Adult Outpatient (PHP)</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Treatment Trails\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/treatment-trails/\">Treatment Trails</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Frequently Asked Questions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/frequently-asked-questions/\">Frequently Asked Questions</a>','Our Programs','','publish','open','open','','our-programs','','','2014-12-21 22:47:15','2014-12-22 03:47:15','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/',10,'page','',0),(16,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','Holly Hill offers several different tracts for our adult patients needing inpatient mental health services. The tract to which the patient is assigned depends on the patients individual diagnosis and treatment care plan. Our ability to house and treat patients based on the needs required by their diagnosis, allows for a more individualized and comfortable treatment experience. The programs address a wide range of concerns including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Depression</li>\r\n	<li>Suicidal Thoughts</li>\r\n	<li>Bi-Polar Disorder</li>\r\n	<li>Schizophrenia</li>\r\n	<li>Anxiety Disorders</li>\r\n	<li>PTSD</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nA typical day on an adult unit includes group therapy, recreation therapy and wellness education. Patients see a psychiatrist and medical doctor throughout their stay and 24-hour nursing care is provided. There are also scheduled times when the patient will meet with his or her therapist individually.\r\n\r\nAs with our other programs, we encourage participation in treatment and discharge planning by the patient’s family or support system.  The adult programs also participate in our <a title=\"Treatment Trails\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/treatment-trails/\">Treatment Trails Programming</a>.\r\n\r\nHolly Hill also offers an outpatient program for adults that provides intensive and supportive therapy for patients who are safe to return home at night. Find out more about our <a title=\"Adult Outpatient (PHP)\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/adult-outpatient-php/\">Partial Hospitalization Program Here</a>.','Mental Health','','publish','open','open','','mental-health','','','2014-12-21 22:36:33','2014-12-22 03:36:33','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/mental-health/',11,'page','',0),(17,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','The Holly Hill med-psych, geriatric program is designed to meet the behavioral health needs of older adults who require supportive medical care. Our geriatric program includes a specialized medical evaluation, an assessment of daily living skills and a full psychosocial assessment and intervention. The program addresses a wide range of concerns including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Depression</li>\r\n	<li>Suicidal Thoughts</li>\r\n	<li>Bi-Polar Disorder</li>\r\n	<li>Schizophrenia</li>\r\n	<li>Anxiety Disorders</li>\r\n	<li>PTSD</li>\r\n	<li>Supportive medical care as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nA typical day on the geriatric unit includes group therapy, recreation therapy and wellness education. Patients see a psychiatrist and medical doctor throughout their stay and 24-hour nursing care is provided. There are also scheduled times when the patient will meet with his or her therapist individually.\r\n\r\nAs with our other programs, we encourage participation in treatment and discharge planning by the patient’s family or support system.  The geriatric program also participates in our <a title=\"Treatment Trails\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/treatment-trails/\">Treatment Trails Programming</a>.','Geriatrics','','publish','open','open','','geriatrics','','','2014-12-21 22:35:16','2014-12-22 03:35:16','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/geriatrics/',12,'page','',0),(18,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','At Holly Hill we recognize alcohol and drug dependencies as a treatable medical illness. Our treatment program for chemical dependency utilizes traditional group therapy combined with a strong, 12-step education component to help our patients begin on their road to recovery. We also provide medically managed detox for must substances. In addition to daily therapy groups, patients will also attend regular NA/AA meetings. As a dual diagnosis program, patients also receive treatment for any underlying psychological disorders that may be at the core of the patient’s addiction.\r\n\r\nAs with our other programs, we encourage participation in treatment and discharge planning by the patient’s family or support system.  The substance abuse recovery program also participates in our <a title=\"Treatment Trails\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/treatment-trails/\">Treatment Trails Programming</a>.','Substance Abuse','','publish','open','open','','substance-abuse','','','2014-12-21 22:32:33','2014-12-22 03:32:33','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/substance-abuse/',13,'page','',0),(19,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','An outpatient program available to adults ages 18 and over, the Holly Hill Partial Hospitalization Program is designed for those who need more support than traditional, once a week therapy, in treating mental health concerns. Specializing in depressive, anxiety, bipolar and personality disorders, the PHP provides patients with 5 day a week access to a psychiatrist, registered nurse and therapist. The program is from 8:45am – 2:15pm, Monday through Friday and allows patients the freedom to receive intensive medication management and therapeutic services, while being able to return home during nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nThe backbone of the program is psychotherapy groups. These groups allow patients to work on problems simultaneously, receive support and feedback from others with similar problems, and provide real life examples of other patients’ behaviors, all within a safe setting for patients to try out new behaviors.\r\n\r\nGroup therapy topics include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coping Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Anger Management</li>\r\n	<li>Family Dynamics</li>\r\n	<li>Spirituality</li>\r\n	<li>Healthy Lifestyles</li>\r\n	<li>Communication Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Stress Trigger Identification &amp;  Response</li>\r\n	<li>Grief &amp; Loss</li>\r\n	<li>Stress Management</li>\r\n	<li>Crisis Management Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Trauma Recovery</li>\r\n	<li>Relaxation Therapy</li>\r\n	<li>Planning for Success</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table style=\"height: 104px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"431\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\" colspan=\"2\" width=\"200\">To schedule a free intake assessment:</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">Monday-Friday</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">Evenings and Weekends</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">8:00am to 5:00pm</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">919.250.7000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">919.250.7307</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">800.447.1800</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','Adult Outpatient (PHP)','','publish','open','open','','adult-outpatient-php','','','2014-12-21 22:30:31','2014-12-22 03:30:31','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/adult-outpatient-php/',14,'page','',0),(20,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','','Treatment Trails','','publish','open','open','','treatment-trails','','','2014-12-22 14:41:14','2014-12-22 19:41:14','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/treatment-trails/',15,'page','',0),(21,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','Holly Hill Hospital strives to provide a serene, comfortable and safe treatment experience for all of our patients. Most of our patients and their families have questions about their stay with us. The most commonly asked questions are below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#inpatient\">What will I need for an inpatient stay at Holly Hill?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#long\">How long can I expect to be in treatment?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#treatment\">What can I expect regarding treatment at Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#team\">Who are the members of the Treatment Team?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#phone\">Can I make and receive phone calls?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#confidential\">Is this confidential?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#expect\">What can I expect during a typical day at Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#visit\">What are visiting hours?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#costs\">What about costs?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#discharge\">What can I expect regarding discharge from Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a id=\"inpatient\"></a>\r\n<h2>What will I need for an inpatient stay at Holly Hill?</h2>\r\nBring 4 to 5 changes of comfortable clothes. Clothes with strings, laces, ties and/or hoods are prohibited. Shoes may not have laces. Slipper socks will be provided if needed.\r\nPersonal hygiene items.\r\nJournal or composition book but no spiral binders.\r\nAppropriate reading material.\r\n<a id=\"long\"></a>\r\n<h2>How long can I expect to be in treatment?</h2>\r\nThe length of treatment varies depending on your reasons for admission, your response to treatment and your progress toward your treatment goals. The average length of stay at Holly Hill Hospital is around 10 days.\r\n<a id=\"treatment\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect regarding treatment at Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\nHolly Hill Hospital provides short-term, acute, crisis stabilization. Like most acute mental health hospitals, we primarily use group therapy as it can be much more effective for acute recovery. The treatment team at Holly Hill Hospital encourages all patients to include their family/significant others in their recovery. The assigned therapist will talk to designated family members and set up a family session, as appropriate to treatment. All patients are on unit restriction for a minimum of 24 hours. At that point, the physician may determine if the patient is safe to attend off-unit activities and eat meals in the cafeteria. Patients are expected to participate in the unit activities unless their attending physician indicates they are too ill to attend programming. Patient phones are not available while groups are in session.\r\n<a id=\"team\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect from the Treatment Team?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Psychiatrist:</strong> He or she directs medical management while at Holly Hill. Patients will be seen by a psychiatrist within the first 24 hours of admission.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Registered Nurses:</strong> Are responsible for daily activities and medical/emotional needs. The RNs participate in behavior management and administer medications as ordered by the physician.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Mental Health Technicians:</strong> Assist with daily activities. They supervise program groups and activities, take vital signs and accompany patients to off unit activities.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Recreation Therapist:</strong> Assists with recreational activities as tools to enhance your self-esteem, problem-solving and social skills.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Social Worker/Therapist:</strong> Organizes discharge plan with the patient, family, psychiatrist and community. The therapist provides group therapy for patients on the unit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Can I make and receive phone calls?</h2>\r\nYes, adults may make calls during most non-therapy times, but please leave cell phones at home. To protect your privacy you will be assigned a confidential ID number at admission. To receive calls from your family or friends they will need to use this number. We ask that family members wait to call until listed phone times so as not to disrupt the treatment program.\r\n<a id=\"confidential\"></a>\r\n<h2>Is this confidential?</h2>\r\nAbsolutely. Rigorously enforced laws of confidentiality help protect your rights to privacy. We cannot confirm or deny your presence in our facility without your written permission.\r\n<a id=\"expect\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect during a typical day at Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\nThe treatment day varies by program but there are many common elements. During the first 24 hours, a patient will have a nursing assessment, a history and physical and a psychiatric evaluation. Daily treatment components include daily doctor visits and group and recreational therapy. Patients with substance abuse issues will <strong>participate</strong> in in-house AA/NA meetings.\r\n\r\nInformation on a day in our Partial Hospitalization Program can be found <a title=\"Adult Outpatient (PHP)\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/our-programs/adult-outpatient-php/\">here</a>.\r\n<a id=\"visit\"></a>\r\n<h2>What are the visiting hours?</h2>\r\nVisiting hours vary by individual unit and can be found <a title=\"Visiting Hours &amp; Phone Times\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/about-our-adult-campus/visiting-hours-phone-times/\">here</a>. (link to visiting hours page) In addition to these scheduled visitation times, you will be allowed to visit following any scheduled family therapy session. Our first priority is the safety of our patients and guests, so we ask that visitors keep all personal items such as purses, bags, or any sharp items in their vehicle as they are not allowed on the units. Outside food and drink is also not allowed and photo ID is required to visit.\r\n<a id=\"costs\"></a>\r\n<h2>What about costs?</h2>\r\nWe are a preferred provider for most commercial insurance plans. We also accept Medicare, Managed Medicaid and TRICARE®. Please call our assessment or business office and they can answer your individual concerns and questions.\r\n<a id=\"discharge\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect regarding discharge from Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Physician’s Order is required before any patient can be discharged from Holly Hill Hospital.</li>\r\n	<li>The treatment team makes a decision regarding discharge date based on patient symptoms and needs. Patients are given an estimated length of stay upon admission. This may change over the hospital stay based on individual needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Patients admitted to Holly Hill Hospital on a voluntary basis, may submit a 72 hour request for discharge at any time. This gives the physician and treatment team a 72 hour time frame to determine if the patient is safe for discharge. Any Holly Hill staff member can supply the patient with the 72 hour request for discharge form.</li>\r\n	<li>All patients are required to have aftercare appointments prior to being discharged. The assigned therapist will coordinate with the patient to connect them to an existing provider or to refer to new services.</li>\r\n	<li>Holly Hill Hospital attempts to complete discharges prior to 11am. Please coordinate transportation on the day of discharge to accommodate this time frame. Notify the assigned therapist as soon as possible if this will not be feasible.</li>\r\n</ul>','Frequently Asked Questions','','publish','open','open','','frequently-asked-questions','','','2014-12-11 15:18:29','2014-12-11 15:18:29','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/frequently-asked-questions/',16,'page','',0),(22,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','','Visiting Hours & Phone Times','','trash','open','open','','visiting-hours-phone-times','','','2014-12-08 19:03:01','2014-12-08 19:03:01','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/our-programs/visiting-hours-phone-times/',17,'page','',0),(23,1,'2014-12-02 21:55:16','2014-12-02 21:55:16','<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">At Holly Hill Hospital, we understand that seeking services for yourself or your loved one can be an overwhelming experience. Our admissions staff can help you better understand which of our programs is best for your needs and help you find a sense of comfort during this time in your life. Each admission staff member can help answer questions about the treatment provided at Holly Hill, the admission procedures and insurance reimbursement.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The assessment center at Holly Hill is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week and provides no-cost, confidential assessments.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><i><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><b>To speak with a Holly Hill admissions counselor please us now at 1-800-447-1800. </b></span></i></span></p>','Admissions & Assessments','','publish','open','open','','admissions','','','2014-12-21 22:29:23','2014-12-22 03:29:23','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/admissions/',18,'page','',0),(24,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:06','2014-12-02 22:02:06','The assessment center at Holly Hill Hospital provides no-cost, confidential mental health assessments seven days a week. Our assessment counselors are caring clinicians, dedicated to helping your find the appropriate services for your mental health and substance abuse needs.\r\n\r\nTo speak with an assessment counselor now, or to schedule an appointment, please call 1-800-447-1800.\r\n\r\nOur facility is conveniently located in Raleigh, North Carolina. For directions please <a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/directions/\">click here</a>.','24/7 Assessment Services','','publish','open','open','','247-assessment-services','','','2014-12-21 22:27:14','2014-12-22 03:27:14','',23,'http://localhost/hollyhill/admissions/247-assessment-services/',19,'page','',0),(25,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:06','2014-12-02 22:02:06','Treatment services are covered in whole or part by most insurance plans and Holly Hill Hospital is a preferred provider for most commercial insurers. We also accept Medicare and Tricare.','Treatment Cost','','publish','open','open','','treatment-cost','','','2014-12-03 21:41:03','2014-12-03 21:41:03','',23,'http://localhost/hollyhill/admissions/treatment-cost/',20,'page','',0),(26,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:06','2014-12-02 22:02:06','','​Frequently Asked Questions','','trash','open','open','','%e2%80%8bfrequently-asked-questions','','','2014-12-08 19:03:55','2014-12-08 19:03:55','',23,'http://localhost/hollyhill/admissions/%e2%80%8bfrequently-asked-questions/',21,'page','',0),(27,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:07','2014-12-02 22:02:07','','Contact Us','','trash','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-08 18:10:13','2014-12-08 18:10:13','',23,'http://localhost/hollyhill/admissions/contact-us/',22,'page','',0),(28,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:07','2014-12-02 22:02:07','Join the team of Holly Hill Hospital, a growing, private, psychiatric facility that has provided over 30 years’ worth of quality care and recovery services to the community. Based in Raleigh, NC, Holly Hill Hospital is perfectly located in a rapidly growing family-oriented community that is just hours from the mountains and the beaches and is a surrounded by major universities. We are privileged to have a rich compliment of dedicated employees.\r\n\r\nHolly Hill Hospital offers competitive compensation and excellent benefits including medical, dental, vision, life, 401K with matching, voluntary supplemental benefits, tuition reimbursement, and paid time off.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://uhs.ats.hrsmart.com/cgi-bin/portal/alljobs.cgi?qty=25&amp;order=jobtitle&amp;companycode=544\" name=\"Holly Hill Hospital Career Opportunities\" width=\"100%\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"1\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"yes\"></iframe>','Careers','','publish','open','open','','careers','','','2014-12-22 14:41:59','2014-12-22 19:41:59','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/careers/',23,'page','',0),(29,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:07','2014-12-02 22:02:07','<h2 class=\"western\">Adult Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 18 and over should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">3019 Falstaff Road</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7000</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax:919.231.5302</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/directions/\">Directions</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"western\">Children’s Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 17 and younger should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">201 Michael J Smith Lane</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7600</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax: 919.250.6724</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/directions/\"><i> Directions</i></a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"western\">[gravityform id=\"1\" name=\"Contact Us\" description=\"false\"]</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">For any concerns regarding Holly Hill Hospital, you may <a title=\"Contact Senior Management\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/contact-senior-management/\">contact senior management</a>. To request access to medical records please complete <a href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Authorization-form-Website.pdf\">this form</a> and mail or fax it to the address and number provided. You may also email the completed form to medical records at <a href=\"mailto:HollyHill.MedicalRecords@uhsinc.com\">HollyHill.MedicalRecords@uhsinc.com</a></p>','Contact Us','','publish','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-21 22:42:12','2014-12-22 03:42:12','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/contact-us/',24,'page','',0),(30,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:07','2014-12-02 22:02:07','<h2>Adult Campuses</h2>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"450\" style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3236.7098890212105!2d-78.58393840000001!3d35.78250209999998!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ac5e95ef0bfdef%3A0xa6328079c96d9c6c!2s3019+Falstaff+Rd%2C+Raleigh%2C+NC+27610!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1415378369610\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<h2>Child &amp; Adolescent Campus</h2>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"450\" style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3236.847224407364!2d-78.57838600000001!3d35.77912899999999!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ac5e976eccd285%3A0x76744f6ee5df2926!2s201+Michael+J+Smith+Ln%2C+Raleigh%2C+NC+27610!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1415378051652\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>','Directions','','publish','open','open','','directions','','','2014-12-09 15:32:31','2014-12-09 15:32:31','',29,'http://localhost/hollyhill/contact-us/directions/',25,'page','',0),(31,1,'2014-12-02 22:02:29','2014-12-02 22:02:29','','Child & Adolescent Campus','','publish','open','open','','child-adolescent-campus','','','2014-12-03 19:40:07','2014-12-03 19:40:07','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/',26,'page','',0),(32,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','Holly Hill Hospital’s Children’s Campus provides excellent <a title=\"Explore Discover Connect\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/explore-discover-connect/\">treatment programs</a> that provide strong communication with families and support systems. These programs can help your child or adolescent get back on the best path to wellness. With a staff of clinicians experienced in the fields of mental health and addiction, Holly Hill is a source of support for our patients, their families and the communities we serve.\r\n\r\nHolly Hill Hospital’s Children’s Campus is designed specifically for kids and adolescents. The treatment is centered around the philosophy that the best behavioral healthcare is comfortable, nurturing and even a little fun. Our hospital provides lots of outdoor play areas including walking trails with exercise equipment, a basketball court and even a playground for our youngest patients. Our staff is able to utilize these outdoor areas, along with indoor activity areas such as a game room and gym, to provide recreational therapy and a reward based treatment program. This treatment model, when coupled with traditional group therapy, can provide a strong backbone of coping skills to help children and adolescents make the best choices after their graduation from Holly Hill.\r\n\r\nThe Holly Hill Hospital Children’s Campus is located at 201 Michael J Smith Lane in Raleigh, North Carolina. All patients 17 and under should come to the children’s campus for assessment and/or admission. Learn more about our adult programs for patients 18 and above <a title=\"About Our Adult Campus\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/about-our-adult-campus/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nFor more information about our mental health or substance abuse treatment programs please call us now at 800-447-1800.','About Our Children’s Campus','','publish','open','open','','about-our-childrens-campus','','','2014-12-22 13:49:48','2014-12-22 18:49:48','',31,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/',27,'page','',0),(33,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<a href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mm-head-shot.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-354 alignright\" src=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mm-head-shot-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"mm-head-shot\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Welcome to Holly Hill Hospital. For over 35 years, the Holly Hill name has been one of comfort and quality and I’m proud to say that we are constantly evolving, growing and enriching our programs to continue in this tradition of providing excellence in clinical behavioral health care.\r\n\r\nIt is our priority at Holly Hill to provide our patients with the treatment and resources needed to return to their communities as healthier individuals. To accomplish this goal I am joined by a team of clinical leaders who are experts in their field and share the vision and passion necessary to provide the best possible programming for the patients in our care. As a community resource, we also provide around the clock, no cost assessments to ensure that those who need services can find the appropriate placement and level of care.\r\n\r\nWe hope that our site provides you with the information you need as you search for help for yourself or loved one. I invite you to contact us today with questions or to receive more information on our programs and treatment team.\r\n\r\n<em>Sincerely,</em>\r\n\r\nMichael S. McDonald, Jr.\r\nChief Executive Officer – Managing Director','​CEO Welcome','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8bceo-welcome','','','2014-12-21 23:24:16','2014-12-22 04:24:16','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/%e2%80%8bceo-welcome/',28,'page','',0),(34,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Programs','','trash','open','open','','programs','','','2014-12-08 19:15:03','2014-12-08 19:15:03','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/programs/',29,'page','',0),(35,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','At Holly Hill Hospital, we encourage families to be an active part of their loved one’s treatment and recovery. Visiting hours and group family sessions are two of the ways you can support a loved one in treatment at our facility.\r\n<h2>General Visitation &amp; Phone Rules</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A confidential ID number is issued to each patient at the time of admission. Due to patient confidentiality, only the legal guardian of a minor patient may give out this number.  Any visitor calling or coming in must have the ID number.</li>\r\n	<li>All visitors will be required to present valid identification prior to visiting.</li>\r\n	<li>No more than 2 visitors are allowed at one time.</li>\r\n	<li>Children under the age of 13 may not visit.</li>\r\n	<li>Phone call duration may be limited based on the therapy schedule. Patients may not make or receive phone calls during group times.</li>\r\n	<li>Day of Discharge: The therapist will coordinate a discharge date based on the individualized treatment plan. Please note that all discharges occur before 11:00am and transportation needs must be arranged prior to that time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>CHILDREN (ages 4-12) and ADOLESCENTS (ages 13 – 17) Visiting Hours and Phone Times:</h3>\r\nVisiting Hours:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Monday – Friday, 6:30 – 8:00 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Saturday, 1:30-3:30 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Sunday, 1:30-3:30 p.m.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPhone Times:\r\n\r\nPhones are available for incoming and outgoing phone calls nightly: 6:30 p.m. – 8:00 p.m.','Visiting Hours & Phone Times','','publish','open','open','','visiting-hours-phone-times','','','2014-12-22 13:54:45','2014-12-22 18:54:45','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/visiting-hours-phone-times/',30,'page','',0),(36,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','At Holly Hill Hospital, we know that it is our people who make the difference in the lives of our patients. Each of our employees, from mental health technicians and nurses to doctors and therapists, have the heart and training to provide consistently excellent care.\r\n\r\nLeading our team of talented individuals is a medical staff of impressive acclaim.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Collectively, our medical staff has over 100 years of psychiatric, inpatient hospital experience.</li>\r\n	<li>All of our psychiatrists have held appointments at University Medical Centers as teachers in psychiatry.</li>\r\n	<li>Our medical staff has published over 40 articles in medical journals.</li>\r\n	<li>In addition to psychiatry, more than half of our medical staff has significant medical care experience including work as emergency care physicians.</li>\r\n	<li>Our medical staff is experienced with treatment in a VA Hospital setting as well as enlisted military treatment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n<h2>Medical Staff:</h2>\r\n<div>[simple-staff-list group=\"Medical Staff\"]</div>\r\n</div>','Our Medical Team','','publish','open','open','','our-medical-team','','','2014-12-22 13:58:03','2014-12-22 18:58:03','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/our-medical-team/',31,'page','',0),(37,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','At Holly Hill Hospital, we understand that seeking services can be an overwhelming experience. Our admissions staff can help you better understand which of our programs is best for your needs and help you find a sense of comfort during this time in your life. Each admission staff member can help answer questions about the treatment provided at Holly Hill, the admission procedures and insurance reimbursement.\r\n\r\n<strong>The assessment center at Holly Hill is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week and provides no-cost, confidential assessments.</strong>','Admissions & Assessments','','publish','open','open','','admissions-assessments','','','2014-12-10 23:22:57','2014-12-10 23:22:57','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/admissions-assessments/',32,'page','',0),(38,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<a href=\"http://www.jointcommission.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-260 alignleft\" src=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/joint-commission-logo.jpg\" alt=\"joint-commission-logo\" width=\"100\" height=\"101\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHolly Hill Hospital is fully licensed by the state of North Carolina and is accredited by the <a href=\"http://www.jointcommission.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Joint Commission</a>.','​Licensing & Accreditation','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8blicensing-accreditation','','','2014-12-22 14:22:14','2014-12-22 19:22:14','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/%e2%80%8blicensing-accreditation/',33,'page','',0),(39,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','Please fill out the form below to make a secure payment to Holly Hill Hospital. Note the First Name and Last Name should be the payer responsible for paying your invoice. If there are any questions or concerns please call us at 800.447.1800.\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\nvar l2pButtonText = \'Pay Now\';\r\nvar l2pCustomWrapperStyles = {\r\n  \"background\": \"#ffffff\",\r\n  \"border-color\": \"#ffffff\",\r\n  \"border-style\": \"solid\",\r\n  \"border-width\": \"2px\",\r\n  \"width\": \"400px\"\r\n};\r\nvar l2pCustomLabelStyles = {\r\n  \"color\" : \"#222222\"\r\n};\r\nvar l2pWidgetCustomFields = {\'fields\':[{\'label\':\'Address\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'City\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'State\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Zip\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Phone\',\'type\':7,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Relationship\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient First Name\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient Last Name\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true},{\'label\':\'Patient Account No\',\'type\':0,\'options\':[],\'required\':true}]};\r\n// do not modify these values!\r\nvar l2pClientId = \'2f2b265625d76a6704b08093c652fd79\';\r\nvar l2pWidgetId = \'1568\';\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n<script id=\"l2p-widget-script\" src=\"https://www.linked2pay.com/l2p/widgets/paymentForm/js/load.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"l2p-widget-wrapper\"></div>','​Pay Your Bill','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8bpay-your-bill','','','2014-12-22 14:25:59','2014-12-22 19:25:59','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/%e2%80%8bpay-your-bill/',34,'page','',0),(40,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Contact Us','','trash','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-04 14:06:50','2014-12-04 14:06:50','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/contact-us/',35,'page','',0),(41,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Careers','','trash','open','open','','careers','','','2014-12-04 14:06:59','2014-12-04 14:06:59','',32,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/about-our-childrens-campus/careers/',36,'page','',0),(42,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','As a leader in behavioral healthcare, Holly Hill Hospital is committed to providing our patients with treatment programs that can help put them on a more solid path to recovery. Patients and their families can expect quality treatment provided by a thoughtful and compassionate staff.\r\n\r\nAll programming at our Children’s Campus is positive, patient-centered and designed to maximize family and support system involvement. <a title=\"Explore Discover Connect\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/explore-discover-connect/\">Learn more here.</a>','Our Programs','','publish','open','open','','our-programs','','','2014-12-22 13:52:51','2014-12-22 18:52:51','',31,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/',37,'page','',0),(43,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<p class=\"western\">The <span style=\"color: #548dd4;\">Explore</span>, <span style=\"color: #c00000;\">Discover</span>, <span style=\"color: #ffc000;\">Connect</span> Phase System is a rewards-based program designed to empower patients to take a proactive role in his or her own treatment. There are three phases leading up to graduation that each patient must complete.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-340\" src=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/explore-discover-connect-300x252.png\" alt=\"explore-discover-connect\" width=\"300\" height=\"252\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Each phase offers specific patient privileges for those who meet the goals and criteria for advancement.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">During <span style=\"color: #0070c0;\">Explore, </span>the patient will answer the questions: “Who am I?” and “Why am I here?” <span style=\"color: #0070c0;\">Explore</span> goals include writing a personal Life Story and being able to recite <span style=\"color: #00b050;\">THE BIG FIVE</span>, a set of basic life values for how we treat others and ourselves.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Once the patient has a stronger understanding of how their personal history has affected him/her up to this point in life, he or she will move into the <span style=\"color: #c00000;\">Discover</span> phase.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">During <span style=\"color: #c00000;\">Discover</span>, the patient will answer the question: “What can I learn?” <span style=\"color: #c00000;\">Discover</span> goals include the identification and explanation of triggers and development of appropriate coping skills.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Once the patient has visualized their ideal life and the steps to take to realize this life, they will move into the <span style=\"color: #ffc000;\">Connect</span> phase. The <span style=\"color: #ffc000;\">Connect </span>phase provides patients the opportunity to develop longer term goals, employ the coping skills they identified during <span style=\"color: #c00000;\">Discover</span> and serve as a role model for their peers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">In order to graduate, the patient must be able to define their diagnoses and list and explain the benefits of any prescribed medications. The patient must also complete a behavioral contract with their parents or guardians and review their Safety Plan with their Therapist.</p>','Explore, Discover, Connect','','publish','open','closed','','explore-discover-connect','','','2014-12-22 14:32:44','2014-12-22 19:32:44','',42,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/explore-discover-connect/',38,'page','',0),(44,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','Holly Hill Hospital encourages families and support systems to be an active part of their child’s treatment and recovery. We provide family therapy sessions, multi-family educational workshops and ample visitation hours to encourage participation.\r\n\r\nFor families outside of the Raleigh area, we have arranged options for easy overnight accommodations at area hotels. Parents of children under 18 may also qualify for a stay at our local Ronald McDonald House. We are also able to provide family therapy using phone conferencing and in some cases telehealth services. Ask a Holly Hill counselor for details.','Family Involvement','','publish','open','open','','family-involvement','','','2014-12-22 14:28:55','2014-12-22 19:28:55','',42,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/family-involvement/',39,'page','',0),(45,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','Holly Hill Hospital strives to provide a serene, comfortable and safe treatment experience for all of our patients. Most of our patients and their families have questions about their stay with us. The most commonly asked questions are below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#need\">What will I need for an inpatient stay at Holly Hill?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#long\">How long can I expect to be in treatment?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#treatment\">What can I expect regarding treatment at Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#team\">Who are the members of the Treatment Team?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#phone\">Can I make and receive phone calls?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#confidential\">Is this confidential?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#day\">What can I expect during a typical day at Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#visiting\">What are visiting hours?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#costs\">What about costs?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#discharge\">What can I expect regarding discharge from Holly Hill Hospital?</a>\r\n<a id=\"need\"></a>\r\n<h2>What will I need for an inpatient stay at Holly Hill?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bring 4 to 5 changes of comfortable clothes. Clothes with strings, laces, ties and/or hoods are prohibited. Shoes may not have laces. Slipper socks will be provided if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Personal hygiene items.</li>\r\n	<li>Journal or composition book but no spiral binders.</li>\r\n	<li>Appropriate reading material.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>How long can I expect to be in treatment?</h2>\r\nThe length of treatment varies depending on your reasons for admission, your response to treatment and your progress toward your treatment goals. The average length of stay at Holly Hill Hospital is around 10 days.\r\n<a id=\"treatment\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect regarding treatment at Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\nHolly Hill Hospital provides short-term, acute, crisis stabilization. Like most acute mental health hospitals, we primarily use group therapy as it can be much more effective for acute recovery. The treatment team at Holly Hill Hospital encourages all patients to include their family in their recovery. The assigned therapist will talk to designated family members and set up a family session, as appropriate to treatment. All patients are on unit restriction for a minimum of 24 hours. At that point, the physician may determine if the patient is safe to attend off-unit activities and eat meals in the cafeteria. Patients are expected to participate in the unit activities unless their attending physician indicates they are too ill to attend programming. Patient phones are not available while groups are in session.\r\n<a id=\"team\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect from the Treatment Team?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Psychiatrist: He or she directs medical management while at Holly Hill. Patients will be seen by a psychiatrist within the first 24 hours of admission.</li>\r\n	<li>Registered Nurses: Are responsible for daily activities and medical/emotional needs. The RNs participate in behavior management and administer medications as ordered by the physician.</li>\r\n	<li>Mental Health Technicians: Assist with daily activities. They supervise program groups and activities, take vital signs and accompany patients to off unit activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Recreation Therapist: Assists with recreational activities as tools to enhance your self-esteem, problem-solving and social skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Social Worker/Therapist: Organizes discharge plan with the patient, family, psychiatrist andcommunity. The therapist provides group therapy for patients on the unit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Can I make and receive phone calls?</h2>\r\nYes, phone calls can be made during specified phone times, but please leave cell phones at home. To protect privacy the patient will be assigned a confidential ID number at admission. To receive calls family and support systems will need to use this number. We ask that family members wait to call until listed phone times so as not to disrupt the treatment program.\r\n<a id=\"confidential\"></a>\r\n<h2>Is this confidential?</h2>\r\nAbsolutely. Rigorously enforced laws of confidentiality help protect rights to privacy. We cannot confirm or deny presence in our facility without written permission.\r\n<a id=\"day\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect during a typical day at Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\nThe treatment day varies by unit but there are many common elements. During the first 24 hours, a patient will have a nursing assessment, a history and physical and a psychiatric evaluation. Daily treatment components include daily doctor visits and group and recreational therapy.\r\n<a id=\"visiting\"></a>\r\n<h2>What are the visiting hours?</h2>\r\n<h3>CHILDREN (ages 4-12) and ADOLESCENTS (ages 13 – 17) Visiting Hours and Phone Times:</h3>\r\nVisiting Hours:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Monday – Friday, 6:30 – 8:00 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Saturday, 1:30-3:30 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Sunday, 1:30-3:30 p.m.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPhone Times:\r\n\r\nPhones are available for incoming and outgoing phone calls nightly: 6:30 p.m. – 8:00 p.m.\r\n\r\nIn addition to these scheduled visitation times, you will be allowed to visit following any scheduled family therapy session. Our first priority is the safety of our patients and guests, so we ask that visitors keep all personal items such as purses, bags, or any sharp items in their vehicle as they are not allowed on the units. Outside food and drink is also not allowed and photo ID is required to visit.\r\n<a id=\"costs\"></a>\r\n<h2>What about costs?</h2>\r\nWe are a preferred provider for most commercial insurance plans. We also accept Medicare, Managed Medicaid and TRICARE®. Please call our assessment or business office and they can answer your individual concerns and questions.\r\n<a id=\"discharge\"></a>\r\n<h2>What can I expect regarding discharge from Holly Hill Hospital?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Physician’s Order is required before any patient can be discharged from Holly Hill Hospital.</li>\r\n	<li>The treatment team makes a decision regarding discharge date based on patient symptoms and needs. Patients are given an estimated length of stay upon admission. This may change over the hospital stay based on individual needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Legal Guardians of minor patients admitted to Holly Hill Hospital on a voluntary basis, may submit a 72 hour request for discharge at any time. This gives the physician and treatment team a 72 hour time frame to determine if the patient is safe for discharge. Any Holly Hill staff member can supply the 72 hour request for discharge form.</li>\r\n	<li>All patients are required to have aftercare appointments prior to being discharged. The assigned therapist will coordinate with the patient to connect them to an existing provider or to refer to new services.</li>\r\n	<li>Holly Hill Hospital attempts to complete discharges prior to 11am. Please coordinate transportation on the day of discharge to accommodate this time frame. Notify the assigned therapist as soon as possible if this will not be feasible.</li>\r\n</ul>','Frequently Asked Questions','','publish','open','open','','frequently-asked-questions','','','2014-12-22 14:31:38','2014-12-22 19:31:38','',42,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/frequently-asked-questions/',40,'page','',0),(46,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Visiting Hours & Phone Times','','trash','open','open','','visiting-hours-phone-times','','','2014-12-08 19:15:56','2014-12-08 19:15:56','',42,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/our-programs/visiting-hours-phone-times/',41,'page','',0),(47,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','At Holly Hill Hospital, we understand that seeking services for yourself or your loved one can be an overwhelming experience. Our admissions staff can help you better understand which of our programs is best for your needs and help you find a sense of comfort during this time in your life. Each admission staff member can help answer questions about the treatment provided at Holly Hill, the admission procedures and insurance reimbursement.\r\n\r\n<strong>The assessment center at Holly Hill is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week and provides no-cost, confidential assessments. Call us today 1-800-447-1800</strong>','Admissions & Assessments','','publish','open','open','','admissions','','','2014-12-22 14:03:09','2014-12-22 19:03:09','',31,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/admissions/',42,'page','',0),(48,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','The assessment center at Holly Hill Hospital provides no-cost, confidential mental health assessments seven days a week. Our assessment counselors are caring clinicians, dedicated to helping your find the appropriate services for your mental health and substance abuse needs.\r\n\r\nTo speak with an assessment counselor now, or to schedule an appointment, please call 1-800-447-1800.\r\n\r\nOur facility is conveniently located in Raleigh, North Carolina. For directions please <a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/directions/\">click here</a>.','24/7 Assessment Services','','publish','open','open','','247-assessment-services','','','2014-12-21 23:22:09','2014-12-22 04:22:09','',47,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/admissions/247-assessment-services/',43,'page','',0),(49,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','Treatment services are covered in whole or part by most insurance plans and Holly Hill Hospital is a preferred provider for most commercial insurers. We also accept Medicare and Tricare.','​Treatment Cost','','publish','open','open','','%e2%80%8btreatment-cost','','','2014-12-22 16:10:04','2014-12-22 21:10:04','',47,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/admissions/%e2%80%8btreatment-cost/',44,'page','',0),(50,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Frequently Asked Questions','','trash','open','open','','frequently-asked-questions','','','2014-12-08 20:41:04','2014-12-08 20:41:04','',47,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/admissions/frequently-asked-questions/',45,'page','',0),(51,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','','Contact Us','','trash','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-08 19:01:57','2014-12-08 19:01:57','',47,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/admissions/contact-us/',46,'page','',0),(52,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<p>Join the team of Holly Hill Hospital, a growing, private, psychiatric facility that has provided over 30 years’ worth of quality care and recovery services to the community. Based in Raleigh, NC, Holly Hill Hospital is perfectly located in a rapidly growing family-oriented community that is just hours from the mountains and the beaches and is a surrounded by major universities. We are privileged to have a rich compliment of dedicated employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Holly Hill Hospital offers competitive compensation and excellent benefits including medical, dental, vision, life, 401K with matching, voluntary supplemental benefits, tuition reimbursement, and paid time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"600\" height=\"500\" name=\"Holly Hill Hospital Career Opportunities\" frameborder=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"1\" scrolling=\"yes\" src=\"https://uhs.ats.hrsmart.com/cgi-bin/portal/alljobs.cgi?qty=25&order=jobtitle&companycode=544\"></iframe>','Careers','','publish','open','open','','careers','','','2014-12-09 15:29:05','2014-12-09 15:29:05','',31,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/careers/',47,'page','',0),(53,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<h2 class=\"western\">Children’s Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 17 and younger should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">201 Michael J Smith Lane</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7600</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax: 919.250.6724</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/directions/\"><i>Directions</i></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"western\">Adult Campus</h2>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><i>Only patients 18 and over should come to this address for assessments and admissions.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">3019 Falstaff Road</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Raleigh, NC 27610</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Phone: 919.250.7000</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Admissions Fax:919.231.5302</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><a title=\"Directions\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/contact-us/directions/\">Directions</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"western\">[gravityform id=\"1\" name=\"Contact Us\" description=\"false\"]</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">For any concerns regarding Holly Hill Hospital, you may <a title=\"Contact Senior Management\" href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/contact-senior-management/\">contact senior management</a>. To request access to medical records please complete <a href=\"http://hollyhill.stage.towermarketing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Authorization-form-Website.pdf\">this form</a> and mail or fax it to the address and number provided. You may also email the completed form to medical records at <a href=\"mailto:HollyHill.MedicalRecords@uhsinc.com\">HollyHill.MedicalRecords@uhsinc.com</a></p>','Contact Us','','publish','open','open','','contact-us','','','2014-12-22 14:27:40','2014-12-22 19:27:40','',31,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/',48,'page','',0),(54,1,'2014-12-02 22:15:22','2014-12-02 22:15:22','<h2>Child &amp; Adolescent Campus</h2>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"450\" style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3236.847224407364!2d-78.57838600000001!3d35.77912899999999!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ac5e976eccd285%3A0x76744f6ee5df2926!2s201+Michael+J+Smith+Ln%2C+Raleigh%2C+NC+27610!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1415378051652\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<h2>Adult Campus</h2>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"450\" style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3236.7098890212105!2d-78.58393840000001!3d35.78250209999998!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ac5e95ef0bfdef%3A0xa6328079c96d9c6c!2s3019+Falstaff+Rd%2C+Raleigh%2C+NC+27610!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1415378369610\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>','Directions','','publish','open','open','','directions','','','2014-12-21 23:18:32','2014-12-22 04:18:32','',53,'http://localhost/hollyhill/child-adolescent-campus/contact-us/directions/',49,'page','',0),(56,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','56','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=56',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(57,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','57','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=57',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(59,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','59','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=59',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(60,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','60','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=60',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(62,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','62','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=62',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(63,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','63','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',5,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=63',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(66,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','66','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',0,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=66',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(67,1,'2014-12-02 22:18:15','2014-12-02 22:18:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','67','','','2014-12-08 18:59:31','2014-12-08 18:59:31','',15,'http://localhost/hollyhill/?p=67',12,'nav_menu_item','',0),(68,1,'2014